text:
Tax officers got the right to request absolutely any documents from firms and entrepreneurs

01 Nov 2019, 07:35

From April 1, 2020, the Tax Code comes into force, giving tax authorities additional rights with respect to taxpayers who owe more than 1 million rubles.

Tax officials were given the right to inspect your premises, things and documents

If the organization or individual entrepreneur does not pay off tax debt within 10 days from the date of the decision of the Federal Tax Service, the tax authorities have the right to request the documents they need from both the taxpayer and third parties.
The list of these documents has recently been developed by the Ministry of Finance.
The project is posted on the federal portal.
The list of documents is as follows:
- documents establishing ownership of real estate, land, vehicles, etc .;
- documents (contracts) for the sale of fixed assets, raw materials, lease and leasing agreements;

Disable Ads

- documents confirming the existence of an exclusive right to a trademark, know-how, etc .;
- accounting registers, balance sheets in the context of accounting accounts (account analytics);
- acts of inventory of property; inventory cards and inventories of fixed assets, inventory items, intangible assets; accounting cards for intangible assets and materials, settlements with customers, suppliers and other debtors and creditors (acts of reconciliation of mutual settlements);
- documents confirming the fact of the performance of work, the provision of services, transfer of rights (acts), certificates of the cost of the work performed, waybills, waybills, invoices for payment, etc .;
- licenses for activities subject to licensing;
- acts of transfer of issued and received bills, bonds, shares, stocks, debt securities;

Disable Ads

- orders to write off receivables that are impossible to collect;
- information on the availability of litigation, the obligations of which are not fulfilled;
- information about the objects of fixed assets used in entrepreneurial activity, indicating the residual value of the objects on the date of submission of documents (information);
- information on objects of inventories, tangible and wearing items, goods, finished products, securities owned by the individual entrepreneur and used by him in entrepreneurial activity on the date of submission of documents (information);
- information on debtors and creditors of the individual entrepreneur indicating the balance of the outstanding obligation;
- business correspondence (letters, messages, notifications of the presence / repayment of debts, claims), or other documents related to the obligations of the taxpayer;

Disable Ads



-


other documents.


Pay attention to the last paragraph of the list, which, in principle, makes this entire list meaningless, since in the end, the Federal Tax Service Inspectorate can request any documents that fit the “other” criterion.



